                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/398a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Chinese Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="35" xml:id="d503fn35">Handed to the Chinese Minister by the Chief of
                        the Division of Far Eastern Affairs, January 26.</note>
                </head>
                <p>Up to the present time the American Government, although it has made informally
                    suggestions toward that end, has not received from the Chinese Government data
                    indicating in any detail and with any particular exactness the character and the
                    extent of the adverse effects which the silver purchasing program of the United
                    States is said to be causing in China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-26">January 26,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
